		on Wednesday January 24, 2024 @08:42AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23203079&amp;cid=64184217">#64184217</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64184217"><p><div class="quote"><p>"diagnosing the condition is currently more valuable if you don't have it."</p></div><p>Let's assume there's no way to slow its progression, early diagnosis is still useful for a number of reasons. For one thing, you'd know that the cognitive decline is going to get worse over time and therefore can take life actions to prepare for it such as checking things off the bucket list and ensuring you have optimal long term care. There's also some level of closure (not sure if that's the right word) in that you (and your family) know what's happening.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64184217">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64184217" class="btn link" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23203079&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64184217" onclick="D2.replyTo(64184217); return false;">Reply to This</a> <span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23203079&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=64184189" onclick="return D2.selectParent(64184189)">Parent</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
