"High accuracy was observed in identifying elevated A (area under the curve [AUC], 0.92-0.96; 95% CI, 0.89-0.99) and tau pathology (AUC, 0.93-0.97; 95% CI, 0.84-0.99) across all cohorts."
</p><p>
So I personally wouldn't go making immediate end of life plans based on this test, but a test indicating Alzheimer's would suggest looking for signs of decline more carefully.  A test saying you<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
